options:
  --ledger-bucket
  --data-bucket-prefix
  --profile
  --mfa-arn

.sackerrc
.sackersession

sacker gc
sacker init

sacker list     [<package prefix>]
sacker versions <package>
sacker info     <package> <spec>

sacker add      <package> <filename>
sacker download <package> <spec> [-o <filename>]
sacker remove   <package> <generation>

sacker tag      <package> <generation> <tag>
sacker untag    <package> <generation> <tag>
sacker tags     <package>

  - n.b. each tag name (e.g. "live", "dev") can be set per package
  - sacker tag chatman 3 live
  - sacker tag chatman 4 live --> live is moved from 3 to 4

/ <data-bucket> / <sha>

/ <ledger-bucket> / .names / <package names>   # index
/ <ledger-bucket> / <b64 package name>         # reserve for future use e.g. sse-c

/ <ledger-bucket> / package name / tags / <tagname>
/ <ledger-bucket> / package name / generations / <number>

metadata in tags:
  { 'generation': 23 }

metadata in generation:
  { 'sha': <str>, 'basename': <str>, 'mode': 0755 }

probably useful:
  user
  date

note: db/<sha> replicated to multiple regions but packages single region
for the sake of consistency?

dynamo ledger:
  dynamo://{table-prefix}
  -> {table-prefix}-generations
  -> {table-prefix}-tags

generations table
  - {package : generation} -> {sha:, basename:, mode:, metadata:{}}

tags table
  - {package : tag} -> {value:, metadata:{}}
